Pop a large #saucepan{} of water onto boil with @salt{1/4%tsp}. We will use it later
for the pasta. Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1} into small pieces. Peel and grate
the @garlic clove{2}(grated with garlic press). Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).

Heat a splash of @oil{1%splash} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Add the
@British pork and oregano sausage meat{225%g} to the pan, and cook until browned,
~{5-6%minutes}, using a #wooden spoon{} to break it up as it cooks.

Add the onion to the sausage and cook until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}, stirring
occasionally. Add the garlic and @Provencal herbs{1}. Stir and cook until fragrant,
~{1%minute}. Add the @tomato puree{30%g}, stir and cook for a further ~{2%minutes}.

Pour the @finely chopped tomatoes{1} into your pan, stir together and allow the
ragu to simmer gently until reduced and thickened, ~{12-15%minutes}. Season with
salt and @pepper{to taste}.

> Add a sprinkle of sugar too (if you have some), it will really lift the flavour of
> the tomatoes.

> IMPORTANT: The sausage meat is cooked when no longer pink.

While your ragu is cooking, add the @pappardelle{200} to the boiling water and cook
until tender, ~{10%minutes}. Do any washing up while everything cooks!

Once cooked, drain the pasta in a #colander{} and drizzle over a little @olive oil{}
to stop it sticking together. Add the pasta to your ragu along with half of the
parsley and half the @hard Italian style cheese{40%g}(grated). Toss together. Serve on
plates and top with the remaining parsley and grated hard Italian style cheese.
Buon appetito!